This is my mid 2024 market view, into 2025, and we will talk about: Bitcoin, S&P500, DXY, FED rates and the potential recession that should come

Hint: it's smaller than any bear's wife's pussy, but still bigger than any bear's penis

Enough! Let's begin!

1. S&P500 index & FED Rates

Ahh, a story as old as time, or a bear's insuccess

FED Rates are a lagging indicator to know how hot the markets are, but still they give a pretty good tell for when there will be problems.

a) September 2007: after 1 year of maintaining rates at 525 bps, we have the first cut, and after 5 more cuts, market was still pretty hot, no sign of recession and big drawdowns.

After those 6 cuts, the soft landing narrative installs - "market no dump bro, we fine, we bid"

Soft landing meant 2-3 FOMC where FED maintained rates again - THIS IS WHERE PROBLEMS START!

During the entire period of cuts, then soft landing - 9 months in total - market remained HOT

b) July 2019: after 6 months of maintaining rates at 250 bps, we have the first cut, and 2 cuts after (Sept and Nov 2019)

After those 3 cuts, soft landing narrative and 2 FOMCs with no rate cuts: Dec & Jan - and big problems in March, 3rd FOMC that brought rates to zero-ish

My guess: this time is not different
Right now we have September 2024 for first rate cut (makes sense after 1y of maintaining rates, just like 2007 high rates of 525 bps, and now 550 bps)

We should have 3-5 rate cuts, which could mean Sept to January-March time, then some soft landing narrative for 2-3 FOMCs with rates maintained, then a global event, again.

SPX up target is $6000ish, down target is $3500+

See my original January 2024 market view, with just the timeline that is different. So basically we could get an extended period of time to reach my targets.

Next up...
2. DXY

Nothing changed on my DXY view, just the timing. Period 3 should come after the "soft landing" narrative, that means the $ printer machine would go berserk like no other time in American history

The Dollar would find its way thru the global economy much easier, much faster, thanks to stablecoins, but this also means double digit inflation on the next wave, 2026+

This would take US assets to a parabolic mania, until end of decade - check my #roaringtwenties posts

3. Bitcoin (& crypto)

Based on the short experience with FED rates, maybe this time could be different (Wall Street owned)

a) 2019 July first cut: as consensus hit the market, euphoria installed, BTC going from 7400$ to 14000$ in a matter of weeks

But then had a downtrend until the soft landing narrative, which meant a last drink before the pandemic war (global event, just like GFC in 2008)

Being a speculative 100 bill $ asset, after the first rate cut, its price action failed to follow the S&P, but that could be different today

b) September 2024 first rate cut: this could differ (maybe we get a July or Nov/December cut, we would update plan later), but we play the hand we're dealt

Either scenario 1 or 2 in play, we're missing a leg up to 90-100k, as euphoria should set in to complete this mid or complete cycle (we will find out later and will update market view)

What I really don't know is if the downtrend after rate cuts is happening this time, ETFs and Wall Street, and the fact that we're at 12x the market cap for BTC as an asset, which makes it nonspeculative

Which could mean that Scenario 2 is in play, so no downtrend until "soft landing" - we shall see

2yrs, 7 drafts & 125,000 words later, The Bushido of Bitcoin is finally available for pre-order.

Writing this book has been a journey, and the process literally transformed my understanding of the world.

This is NOT another history of money or economic justification for Bitcoin. Been there, done that.

This is a book about virtue, excellence, culture and behaviour, which asks the harder questions:

What becomes of those who rise to the top, in the new socio-economic paradigm? 

Will they become:

--> A new kind of parasite?
--> Another bunch of degenerate?
Or
--> Men & women of virtue.

It’s not enough to just say “Bitcoin Fixes This.”
We must do something about it.

____________________

The age of fiat will not last. A new era will take its place. The question is, who will lay claim to it?

IMO: those who understand, that a new age, demands a new way of being. A new paradigm requires a new code, (a Bushido), that’s more vital, powerful and ascendant.

The Bushido of Bitcoin is that playbook.

____________________

This is my attempt to synthesise the best of what I’ve found in both the dissident grass-roots right and philosophy-centric bitcoin domain.

Some of you may be familiar with each other, but many of you will not. I hope this opens some doors and helps form a powerful alliance against the goblins and trolls running the world today.

What people need to understand about #bitcoin is that market cap is a fucking stupid inapplicable metric. 

There many different cohorts of hodlers that assign #bitcoin vastly different values. 

Many hodlers never plan to sell even #BTC below $1 million, much less $100k, $250k or $500k.

But there are plenty of people who bought near the bottom and think one #bitcoin is only worth $65,000. They are selling now.

The market will fuck around here until the cohort willing to sell at around $65,000 sells all their coins.

It will then gap up to the marginal selling price of the next cohort. 

It will go parabolic when coins within a vast range of pussy ass weak hands have been exhausted, and only the most intransigent, @saylor-like never-sellers remain. This will not be linear because this group of sellers believes #bitcoin is not just a little cheap, but vastly under-priced.

This is why the having matters and will continue to matter - because over time, coins make their way - little by little - to the strongest hands. 

The most liquid coins - that need to be sold every damn day to fund mining operations - are the newly mined coins. They therefore count for a *disproportionate share of the marginal liquidity of the current pool of sellers,* even though they are a minuscule proportion of the so-called “market cap.”

They act as a constant downward pressure on price, the relief of which allows for a gap into the hands of the marginal sellers who believe #bitcoin is worth much more than the price at which it currently is selling.

Bitcoin É Um Movimento Político 

Se você investe em bitcoins achando que ele é mais um tipo de investimento, você poderá perder tudo que investiu.

Bitcoin é um movimento político. Nunca se esqueça disto.

Um movimento que ainda está longe de ser vitorioso, tanto que você nem sabia disso.

E se esse movimento falhar, se os movimentos políticos contrários ao sistema Bitcoin vencerem, o valor do bitcoin irá para zero, e você perderá tudo.

É sabido em ciência política de que a forma mais fácil de controlar um povo, é controlando a sua moeda.

Quem controlar a moeda de um país é rei, o ditador, o manda chuva, a classe dominante. 

Políticos sabem disso, por isso contratam economistas para implantar essa forma de poder. Eles imprimem, determinam os juros, endividam países até quebrarem.

O que os políticos não contavam, é que os economistas tomariam assim o poder, sendo os Ministros da Educação, Planejamento, Economia e assim por diante.

I continue to see a huge amount of threads about Binance potential to list new low-mid caps and how it will create millionaires.

Do people actually know that the last few years it has been the complete opposite?

95%+ of Binance listings have dumped 

This is because           
The dynamics of the market has changed.

A Binance listing used to be bullish because we didn't have dexes in the past (not many at least) and neither did we have a lot of cexes.

Effectively it was the only way for retail to get their hands on it.

Today we see uniswap-only tokens running to billions of dollars.

Users also got smarter using these. We don't need Binance anymore like we used to.

We also have 10 tier-1 cex alternatives vs just Binance today.

What Binance does bring to the table?

- The largest listing fees of all and often a huge amount of tokens.

Tokens they will sell and/or listing fee out of the projects budget

- Bigger liquidity

Liquidity for large holders to finally easily cash out because like I said:

Buyers don't need Binance anymore to be able to buy it. Plenty of options out there.

But they will happily use it to sell.

If anything, Binance listings have been a consistent top-signal for the last few years for 95% of tokens out there.

The data is out there and the facts don't lie.

Be careful about the clickbait out there because it's the exact opposite of the reality.

Pre Runes that made it 

Why am I bullish on these? 

The community and distribution 

There are currently 5 in the top 20 MC runes

2. $DOG @LeonidasNFT - 754M
3. $RSIC @rune_coin - 223M
6. $DEC @decentralized02 - 51M
8. $LOBO @lobothewolfpup - 46M
16. $GOB @gob_btc - 9M

They are 2 - 6 on the top holders chart 

This can be both positive and negative, it obviously means possibility of more sellers but supply is spread out between a lot more people

In most cases they had well over a month of trading volume and distribution as Ordinals before runes and so they have hardcore communities that have managed to survive months along with solid distribution 

Another underrated factor is a lot of these are dead wallets that were airdropped runes so might never sell (effectively reducing circulating supply significantly)

I’m super bullish on a bunch of new coins too but the benefit pre runes have is that with a much larger distribution they probably have a greater chance of long-term success compared to coins with less holders which generally dip more in down times

New coins take time to distribute which some of them are doing really well but it takes a lot more volume

For prerunes you can almost add the volume that they traded in Ordinals onto their runes volume 

Obviously not an exact science but people are significantly invested already and so are less likely to just dump at the sight of a small pump

There’s obviously a lot of factors to consider but personally I see these 5 as safer bets than a lot of newer coins purely due to the longevity they’ve already shown 

I love post halvening runes for upside potential but I’ll save that for another tweet
